This Bushmaster rifle is chambered for .223 Remington and 5.56mm NATO rounds and is marked as such, so both may be safely used. There are many that believe that the .223 Remington and the 5.56mm NATO round are the same but in fact they are not. According to Small Arms Manufacturers Institute, Inc, (SAAMI), it is unsafe to fire 5.56mm NATO rounds in firearms chambered for .223 Remington. If you do a little Google searching around the Internet you can find the technical information related to that subject if it interests you. Be careful and only use the ammunition your firearm is designed to fire safely.

title: For Sale:  Saiga Conversion kit, make your plain Saiga look like a AK-47
location: Near Mason City Iowa, Iowa, United States
postcontent:
Sold Payment received.     This Saiga conversion kit is for stamped receivers and includes 1 each, Black Original AK Style Buttstock, Pistol grip with mounting bolt & bushing, trigger guard.  The Saiga Trigger Guard is a bolt on trigger guard for Saiga 7.62x39, 223, 410, 5.45x39, 410 & 20ga Shotguns and most AK47's rifles, it relocates the trigger guard so that you can add a AK pistol grip. This trigger guard is precision laser cut from 16 gauge sheet metal and then formed in a state of the art facility.  It is then de-burred; PEM nuts and stud are inserted, and coated in a durable black powder coat.  The trigger guard kit includes all of the nuts and bolts needed to convert your Saiga to accept AK Pistol grips without the need to drill holes in the receiver except 308. Two new holes must be drilled for the 308 Rifle. The trigger guard attaches to the shotgun using the two rivet holes from the sporter cover plate and the slot from the OEM trigger hole.  The front hole uses an 8-32 stud into the receiver body.  A low profile hex nut attaches to this stud inside the receiver.  The rear two holes use button head screws from inside the receiver to attach the trigger guard.  Width and height of the trigger guard closely mimic a 'standard' AK-47 trigger guard. 

Do not accept Pay Pal being they don't like gun related transactions, everyone should refuse to support businesses who don't support the 2nd Amendment.  Shipping by Priory mail is $12.35, COD is an additional 6.50 for a total of $18.85.

 W.A.S.P. Treated Barrel (Weapon Armament Surface Protection) is a salt bath ferritic nitrocarburizing surface conversion process or more commonly referred to as nitriding.
